courses.learning_outcomes:
a. To pick up skills essential for entrepreneurial success;
b. To demonstrate the ability to plan and work out specifics of an entrepreneurial endeavor; and

c. To present and defend with confidence on their own entrepreneurial or innovative projects.

a. To work effectively on intellectual and practical challenges in a multi-disciplinary team and high uncertainty;

b. Able to translate real-life problems into an approach for problem-solving;

c. To apply knowledge and generate possible solutions, and test these solutions interactively with stakeholders and customers;

d. To creatively combine knowledge, technology, and insight for novel, practical solutions to solve problems in a specific domain or industry;

e. To communicate the solutions and lay out possible implementation plan.
